{"article_id":"1qzNylznzddDGmRG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Now he 's got another historic notch on his belt , the longest-ever government shutdown - an impasse","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that marks a new low for Washington dysfunction .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"The dispute","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"triggered by Trump 's demands for billions of dollars","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"to finally make good on an unfulfilled campaign promise","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"- to build a border wall -","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"began so long ago","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that Republicans had a monopoly on Washington power .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"The Democratic takeover of the House has deepened the disconnect ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"and","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"with neither side willing to fold ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"nearly 22 days in ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"there is still no end in sight .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Since Trump crowed","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"he would be `` proud '' to shutter the government over the wall ,","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"he gets to shoulder much of the blame for a crisis","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"that is the inevitable result","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"when the nation 's political polarization is institutionalized in Washington .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"The last three weeks have exposed the lack of empathy of a billionaire President","depth":4},{"id":19,"text":"who shrugs off the struggles of federal workers","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"who work paycheck to paycheck .","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"Trump is clearly more concerned about a pet political project than his constitutional role","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"of providing governance to all Americans .","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"But he is not alone in his dereliction of duty .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"The Republican-led Senate is doing nothing","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"to offer its President a face saving way out .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"while House Democrats are going through the motions","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"of passing bills","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"to reopen government ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"they do n't seem to be doing much else","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"to break the logjam .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Before Trump was President ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"party leaders had seemed at least open to funding a barrier on the border as part of wider immigration legislation .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Trump urged party leaders Friday to return to Washington","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"and vote for a wall , a barrier or whatever they want to call it","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"-- even `` peaches . ''","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"`` This is where I ask the Democrats to come back to Washington","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"and to vote for money for the wall , the barrier , whatever you want to call it ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"it 's OK with me , ''","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"the President said during a White House roundtable on immigration .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"`` They can name it whatever .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"They can name it 'peaches .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"' I do n't care what they name it .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"But we need money for that barrier , ''","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"he added .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The stalemate represents a crucial first fight between Trump and his Democratic enemies in Washington 's new era of divided government .","depth":3},{"id":47,"text":"But every battle has victims .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"And right now it 's 800,000 government workers","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"who feel insulted , forgotten and anxious about rent , mortgage , car payment and medical bills","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"piling up .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"While they fret ,","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"nothing is happening in Washington this weekend .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"In fact , members of Congress ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"who are getting paid ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"are off until Monday .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"They might notice","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"as they fly home","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that the nation 's transportation system is under strain .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Many of those TSA agents","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"who keep travelers safe","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"are working without pay .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"An airport in Tampa is opening a food bank for employees .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"And some food inspections are on hold with government shut down .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"`` I would beg both Houses of Congress , I would beg the American people to please look around and understand","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that federal workers , we have a face -","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"we have families , ''","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Jacqueline Maloney , a federal worker","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"whose paycheck did n't arrive on Friday ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"told CNN 's Brooke Baldwin in an emotional interview .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"`` We might be a neighbor , your best friend , your best friend 's mom , your aunt , your cousin .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"We are everywhere . ''","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Government shutdowns usually end","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"when the political leaders","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"caught in the standoff","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"calculate","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"that the political damage","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"sustained","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"by standing firm","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"begins to outweigh the embarrassment of a climbdown .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"With tales of anger and deprivation of government workers","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"stuck in a terrible situation beyond their control","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"now dominating news coverage ,","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"that point may be coming closer .","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"Neither side however is showing any sign","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"of cracking yet .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"But for Trump , there would have been no shutdown .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"The President ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"apparently fearing a backlash in conservative media ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"refused to keep the government open before Christmas","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"unless he got wall funding .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"In the last week , Trump has tried a variety of political stunts","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"to try to shift the blame .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"He gave an Oval Office address .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"He stormed out of talks with Democratic leaders .","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"He flew Air Force One to the border","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"to paint an inaccurate picture of hordes of criminals and killers","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"pouring into the country .","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"`` The only way","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"you will stop it","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"is with a very powerful wall or steel barrier , ''","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Trump said at the White House on Friday .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Now ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"as he seeks taxpayer cash","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"to build a wall","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"that he promised","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"Mexico would pay for ,","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"the President is offering the fact-bending claims","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"that America 's neighbor has already settled up","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"-- in a yet to be ratified new trade deal .","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"By any conventional measure , Trump is guilty of putting his own political ego above the interests of the Americans","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"he leads .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"For all the power of his campaign trail rhetoric among supporters , he 's not shifted the political needle at all .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"He seems oblivious that in divided government , a President ca n't just demand what he wants .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Trump 's supporters argue","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"that there is a genuine crisis on the border","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"and brand as `` fake news '' any argument","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"that a wall along the frontier with Mexico may not be the best way","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"to tackle drug trafficking and ballooning asylum claims .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"In fact , the wall has become such an emotional center of Trump 's relationship with his political base","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"- and such a symbol of antipathy towards the President for those","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"who oppose him -","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"that it 's become an insoluble issue .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"`` The bottom line is there is no excuse for the political stunt","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"just because the President had made a commitment","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"when he ran for office and afterwards , ''","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"said Michael Bloomberg , the former New York mayor , in a CNN interview .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"`` He can not get it done","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"and deliver for his constituency .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"He should just stand up","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"and say","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"I tried","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"and let 's get on with the next thing , ''","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"said Bloomberg , a possible 2020 Democratic presidential candidate .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"`` There 's no one issue or one constituency .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"The President has not been elected","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"to be the representative of a party , or of a small group ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"he 's supposed to be representative of a whole country . ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"So far , Trump has held off on his threat","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"to declare a national emergency","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"and reprogram Pentagon funds","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"- possibly from disaster relief projects in Puerto Rico and Texas -","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"to finance his wall .","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"Such a step might allow him to declare a victory","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"that most people will believe to be hollow .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"He might be able to sell his supporters on a battle in the courts after an almost certain legal challenge","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"and reap political capital .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"But it would also represent a fundamental flouting of constitutional governance ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"since a future president ,","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"thwarted by Congress","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"fulfilling its core task","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"of deciding how taxpayer money is spent ,","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"could choose to go ahead with a favorite political project regardless .","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"The failure of Congress","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"to unpick the deadlock","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"has disgusted some of its most venerable members .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"`` How can we resolve this ?","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"We owe it to the American people .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"This is like a circus , ''","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"Republican Sen. Richard Shelby of Alabama said earlier in the week .","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"McConnell has refused to act on Democratic House bills","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"to open various government agencies ,","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"since Trump will not agree to sign them .","depth":8},{"id":163,"text":"For now , McConnell has no desire","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"to open cracks in the Republican coalition","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"by breaking with a President","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"who has leveraged his devoted base","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"to punish any dissidents in his party .","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"There could come a time , however ,","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"when clear discomfort among some GOP members , like Colorado Sen. Cory Gardner , Alaska 's Sen. Lisa Murkowski and Maine 's Sen. Susan Collins , begins to make life uncomfortable for McConnell .","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"The bitterness of shutdown politics has also revealed a seam of hypocrisy","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"that festers on both sides of the aisle in this fractured political age .","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"In 2016 , Republican Sen. Lindsey Graham signed on to an amicus brief in a Supreme Court case","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"challenging President Barack Obama 's use of executive power","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"to shield recipients of the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program from deportation .","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"The document complained","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"that Obama 's move was an attempt","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"to supplant Congress ' power","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"and a threat to the constitutional principle of separation of powers .","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"Those norms seem less important to the South Carolinian","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"now Trump is in the White House .","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"`` Mr. President ,","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"Declare a national emergency NOW .","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"Build a wall NOW , ''","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"Graham tweeted on Friday","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"after meeting Trump .","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"Part of Graham 's frustration stems from his belief","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"that Democrats are hypocrites","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"for refusing to contemplate immigration enforcement policies","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"that they have favored in the past .","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"Early last year , Democrats and the White House appeared close to a deal","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"that would have given Trump $ 25 billion in border security in return for a path to citizenship for DACA recipients","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"-","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"undocumented migrants","depth":15},{"id":194,"text":"brought to the US illegally as children .","depth":15},{"id":195,"text":"The idea of border fencing , or a wall in some areas , has not been so radioactive for Democrats in the past .","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"In 2006 , Democrats","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"including now-Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer and then-Sens . Hillary Clinton and Barack Obama","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"voted to authorize a secure fence along about 700 miles of the US-Mexico border .","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"The project was far from the concrete or steel wall","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"envisioned by Trump .","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"given the symbolic potency of the idea of a wall ,","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"it 's not clear Democrats","depth":15},{"id":204,"text":"-","depth":16},{"id":205,"text":"who do not want their first act in the majority in the House to be a concession to Trump ,","depth":16},{"id":206,"text":"would contemplate any such plan today .","depth":14}],"relations":[{"parent":413,"left":252,"right":412,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":224,"right":251,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":219,"right":223,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":208,"right":218,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":213,"right":217,"rel